<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>The ex-wife of Amazon founder Jeff Bezos has become the richest woman in the world after the astonishing rise in the company’s share price.</p>

<p>Mackenzie Scott, who divorced Bezos last year, is now worth £50.4billion. That makes her worth more than L’Oreal heiress Francoise Bettencourt Meyers, whose fortune totals £49.6billion, according to the Bloomberg Billionaires Index.</p>

<p>The next wealthiest woman is Walmart heiress Alice Walton, who is worth an estimated £47.6billion.</p>

<p>Power couple: Amazon founder Jeff Bezos and ex wife Mackenzie Scott before their divorce last year</p>

<p>Bezos and Scott met in 1992 when she was his assistant at a company called DE Shaw, and were married from 1993 to 2019.</p>

<p>As part of their divorce settlement, mother-of-four Scott, 50, was awarded a quarter of Bezos’s stake in Amazon. </p>

<p>He still owns more than 10 per cent of the firm and has a £153billion fortune.</p>

<p>The company’s share price has rallied by 91 per cent this year as US tech shares soared.</p>

<p>The online ecommerce giant raked in £750million a day on average between April and June, when lockdowns were in force in many Western countries.</p>
